# Translation Sync Rule

When editing translation strings, keep all supported locale files in sync in the same change.

- Supported locales currently include `src/locales/en-US.json` and `src/locales/es-ES.json`.
- If a key is added, renamed, moved, or removed in one locale, apply the same structural change to all supported locales.
- If a value is updated in one locale, update the corresponding value in every supported locale before finishing.
- Do not leave temporary missing keys, stale keys, or placeholder values in one locale only.

Before completing translation-related work, verify:

1. Key paths match across all locale files.
2. Changed keys were updated in each supported locale.
3. JSON remains valid in each locale file.
